cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SY

This paper is a bibliometric analysis of the top cited researchers from USA, UK, and China using Google Scholar data. The analysis involves data mining and automated ranking, which suggests that the paper could belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.DL (Digital Libraries): This sub-category deals with the management, organization, and retrieval of digital information, which is relevant to the data mining and analysis aspect of this paper. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category focuses on the retrieval of relevant information from large collections of data, which is also relevant to the analysis of Google Scholar data in this paper. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category deals with the analysis of social and information networks, which could be relevant to the analysis of the research networks of the top cited researchers. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): This sub-category deals with the social and ethical implications of computing, which could be relevant to the discussion of the impact of research and citation metrics on academic careers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): This sub-category deals with the analysis and control of complex systems, which could be relevant to the analysis of the citation dynamics and patterns of the top cited researchers.
